-----------------------------

Skill:  Breed beasts [9548]

Usage:  USE 9548 <beast1> <beast2>
Time:   fourteen days

Attempt to breed the two specified beasts together.  Most wild
beasts will produce offspring when paired with a mate of their
own species.  Occasionally dissimilar beasts may be successfully
crossed.  The result of such an effort is likely to be quite
unnatural.

Possession of both animals to be mated is required.

Any offspring produced will be wild and untamed, but captive to
the beastmater.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Extract venom from ratspider [9549]

Usage:  USE 9549

Required:  one ratspider
Time:      seven days

The alchemist performs a delicate operation to extract the
highly poisonous ratspider venom.

The top of the ratspider's head is removed by inserting a sharp
knife above the head joint and twisting.  Two glands, from which
the ratspider venom is later extracted, are removed from behind
the mandible.

Risk is minimized by taking extreme care when handling the
ratspider.  The ratspider is killed in the process. 

-----------------------------

Skill:  Make potion of slavery [9550]

Usage:  USE 9550

Required:  one ratspider venom
Time:      seven days

The alchemist brews a potion which, when ingested by a character,
causes that character to become a servant of the alchemist.
The unfortunate noble will swear fealty to the alchemist and
promise to do his bidding.

The rare and highly poisonous ratspider venom is used in the
preparation of this potion.  Upon completion, the new potion
will be added to the alchemist's inventory.  The potion will,
of course, be unlabeled.

A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [601], issue
the order:  USE 601.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Brew healing potion [9551]

Usage:  USE 9551

Required:  avinia leaf [65]
Time:      seven days

The alchemist brews a potion of healing.  Any character
ingesting the potion will be immediately healed of any
wounds or other maladies.

Upon completion, the potion will be added to the alchemist's
inventory.  The potion's label will not reveal its purpose.

A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [602], issue
the order:  USE 602.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Brew potion of death [9552]

Usage:  USE 9552

Required:  lana bark [64]
Time:      ten days

The alchemist brews a potion which will cause instant death
to any character which drinks it.

Upon completion, the potion will be added to the alchemist's
inventory.  The potion's label will not reveal its sinister
purpose.

A character wishing to drink the potion should specify it
to the USE order.  For instance, to drink potion [603], issue
the order:  USE 603.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Produce blank scroll [9553]

Usage:  USE 9553

Required:  lana bark
Time:      fourteen days

Produces one blank magicial scroll from one unit of lana bark.
Magical scrolls are useful to magicians, who have the ability
to transcribe spells onto them.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Add ram to galley [9554]

Usage:  USE 9554

Requires:  three workers [11]
           3 lumber [77]
	   1 iron [79]

Time:	   10 days

A galley fitten with a ram is a most effective ocean fighting
vessel.  The oars permit the ship to be maneuvered in battle,
regardless of wind conditions.  The ram allows a galley to crush
the sides of enemy ships.

To use this skill, the character must enter the galley and issue
USE 9554.  The galley will be fitted with an iron-tipped ram.
The character need not be in control of the ship in order to
perform the modification.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Make pike [9558]

Usage:  USE 9558

Requires:  one lumber [77]
Produces:  one pike [75]
Time:      three days

The pike a simple weapon often used by unskilled soliders, but
nevertheless effective at impaling enemeies or unseating horsemen
when used by coordinated groups of men.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Make longsword [9559]

Usage:  USE 9559

Requires:  one iron [79]
Produces:  one longsword [74]
Time:      seven days

The longsword is a common weapon among soldiers and mercenaries.
Iron is heated over a forge and hammered by the craftsman into
shape.  The blade is quenched in cold water, and the edge sharpened
on a smooth stone wheel.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Make plate armor [9560]

Usage:  USE 9560

Requires:  three iron [79]
Produces:  one plate armor [73]
Time:      fourteen days

The most effective defensive covering, plate armor is fashioned
from iron sheets cut and folded to form a protective suit.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Make longbow [9561]

Usage:  USE 9561

Requires:  one yew [68]
Produces:  one longbow [72]
Time:      twelve days

Longbows are fashioned from long strips of yew wood cut, smoothed,
warped and then glued together.  True to their name, longbows may
be taller than the archers who use them.

-----------------------------

Skill:  Prepare for raid [9571]

Usage:  USE 9571 <target>

This skill improves the chances that a stealth raid, such as
a theft, kidnapping, or assasination, will succeed.  The target
specified is closely studied and spied upon.  Information is
gathered which is useful during a raid, such as defensive
tactics of the target, daily patterns, and state of preparedness.

This skill may only be used on one target at a time, and only
once per month.

The raid must be launched by the end of the month following the
last use of [9571], or the benefits are lost.

The character runs a 5% risk of being caught spying on the enemy
for each use of [9571].  The first use improves the chances of
a successful raid by 10%.  The second, by a further 8%.  The third,
by another 6%.

Further uses give no added benefit, although the state of readiness
will be maintained.  For example, if a character spent three months
using [9571] to prepare for a raid during the fourth month, but
decided for some reason to postpone the raid one month, it would
be wise to use [9571] again to maintain the 24% bonus.  Otherwise
it would be lost.

The target must be present to be spied upon.

-----------------------------

#Skill:  Record skill on scroll [9573]
#
Usage:  USE @@@@ <skill>

Requires:  blank scroll [84]
Time:      seven or more days

Record the given skill on a blank scroll.  The blank scroll will be
consumed, and a new unique scroll will be produced.  The new scroll
will allow one character to learn the skill.

Example:

    USE @@@@ nnnn     # make a one-time study scroll for skill nnnn

Magical skills may not be scribed with this skill.

The skill must be known in order to be written.  If the skill is
rated for experience, a level of "adept" or higher is required to
record the skill.  The character will still know the skill after
writing it.

This skill requires as much time to cast as the skill takes to learn.
Writing a skill which requires two weeks of study to learn will take
two weeks.

